Sentencas: Composite materials Nd0.8Sr1.2CoO4 (-) (delta) - Nd0.5Sr0.5CoO3 (-) (delta) were prepared and evaluated as oxygen electrode for intermediate temperature reversible solid oxide cells (IT-RSOCs).
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of Co-containing mixed oxides as oxygen electrode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide electrolysis cells

Sentencas: Nd0.8Sr1.2CoO4 - (delta) (NSC0812) material with A(2)BO(4-type) structure was prepared by citratenitrate combustion method, and Nd-1 (-) xSrxCoO3 (-) (delta) (x = 0.3, 0.4, 0.5, 0.6, 0.7) materials with perovskite structure were prepared via the glycine nitrate process (GNP).
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of Co-containing mixed oxides as oxygen electrode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide electrolysis cells

Sentencas: The crystal structure, thermal expansion, electrical conductivity and electrochemical properties were investigated.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of Co-containing mixed oxides as oxygen electrode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide electrolysis cells

Sentencas: The lattice volume of Nd1 - xSrxCoO3 (-) (delta) increases with increasing Sr content, x. XRD analysis show that no reaction occurs between oxygen materials and Gd0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (GDC).
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of Co-containing mixed oxides as oxygen electrode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide electrolysis cells

Sentencas: The thermal expansion coefficient increases with increasing x. AC impedance spectroscopy on symmetric cells was used to assess electrochemical performance of the oxygen electrode materials.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of Co-containing mixed oxides as oxygen electrode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide electrolysis cells

Sentencas: Nd0.5Sr0.5CoO3 - (delta) (NSC0505) has the lowest total cathodic polarization resistance for 0.099 Omega cm(2) at 750 degrees C.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of Co-containing mixed oxides as oxygen electrode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide electrolysis cells

Sentencas: The composite materials NSC0505 and NSC0812 with the ratio of 7:3 reveals a better performance than either material individually at 700 degrees C, which is due to introduce of more oxygen vacancies and oxygen interstitials with NSC0812.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance of Co-containing mixed oxides as oxygen electrode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide electrolysis cells

Sentencas: For an electrolysis voltage of 1.3 V, current densities in a single cell fabricated with Nd0.5Sr0.5CoO3 - delta - Nd0.8Sr1.2CoO4 - delta are 420 mA cm(-2) at 800 degrees C. (C) 2016
